<br>
2) You don't log of in Neriak. You get out of Neriak to sell the swords and other stuff that drops. I collected the swords and the gems and didn't bother with the rest. While not extremly good loot, you can bag a fair deal of pp.<br>
<br>
3) Do the fighting on the other side of the bridge on the side with the two wizards. Do the fighting in a circlus. First wizard and second wizard quickly after each other, short breather, go back out and pull the roaming guard with a bolt. You can just reach his spawn point. The guard is the tough fight. The guards also comes in different classes and the SK guard is the toughest even if he doesnt have a pet or use HT. The wizards have a DS (if you give them the time to cast it) and can hurt your pet a lot. This gives you two options. Use cancle magic to remove it or use char to make the wizard dead quick. I used the second, because even if I did get aggro, he tended to cast a lot and if magic resistanse is about 70 you will resist most of it. He may punsh you, and even if he hits rather hard, it will only be one or two hits. Just cook him good with char. You med approximately where the wizards pop.<br>
<br>
4) No chain cast, just use earth pet untill you get lv 53 air. Armor is good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A good idea is to bring a book. Exp is very good, but soon you will kill both the guard and the wizards in about 2 mins, which leaves 5 mins of boredom for meditating and reading a book.<br>
<br>
My result was going from lv 51 to lv 54 with a good safety margin AND 6 AA points. In lv 54 you can propperbly find a better spot for regular exp, but AAXP is still good.<br>
<br>
