<br>
The real difficult part of this is the necromancer.  Going against him, I see the power of the class.  About 60% of the time the necro is a nice smooth encounter (basically, when plays stupid instead of the way another player would fight), the other times he is brutal.  He fears me or, worse, fears my pet.  Once the pet is gone, it's just you, him, and his nasty DoTs.  (once he feared my pet and stacked three DoT's on me - boil blood, scourge, and another).  Some can be gotten rid of with nullify magic (but you're also probably going to lose your good buffs too, i.e. shielding and phantom plate or chain).  Unfortunately, nullify magic doesn't get rid of the poison and disease based DoTs (not sure if the shaman potions that cure disease and poison would work).  My magic resist is 67, disease and poison pretty low - about 35-40 - so if your resists are similar be aware that the necro can rough you up.  Also, make sure you have full hps going into the encounter with the necro - a couple of hundred hps lost in the wizard encounters could be life or death against the necro.  <br>
<br>
I'm in Burning Woods now, but when I go back to Neriak I going to adjust my strategy.   Up to now I've been fighting the necro like a typical mob - send pet in, let it build aggro, nuke.  I'm wondering if I should just nuke the necro hard from the start - the longer he's around, the longer he has to fear my pet or land DoT's.  The necro is rough,  but he gives more xps than either of the two wizzies.  The other option is to start doing the guard instead of the necro - might check that out.  A 400 hp lifetap I can deal with, stacking DoT's are another matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 2:35:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Neriak Casters</span><hr size=1> You need to get your resists up.  At 51, I invested in a full line of BD resist gear, which put my MR to 129, PR/DR slightly lower.  With those resists, the wizzies and necro rarely landed anything on me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 11:02:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Took the easy way out</span><hr size=1> Did Burning Woods, Seafurbies, and Scarlet Desert to 