<br>
While the are busy trying to root you and other stupid crap you're busy completely killing them. Let me clarify why this works a little more... In the time it takes them to nuke you twice you will get off three Scars which is almost always (unless you get really bad resists) enough to have them in run mode or dead <br>
<br>
Depending on your pet (I used fire for it's DS then Air for the stuns then water for the BS'ing and gave them all lava shield) and how it nukes and how much the casters decide to hit or cast the wizzies and necro USUALLY go into run mode after 3 scars if they're not outright dead. I didn't really like earth too much since it takes too much beating when the mobs are in run mode. Not to mention casters not going into run mode means they keep casting on you and that can be major bad.<br>
<br>
Things to note:<br>
<br>
ALWAYS have up shielding and be wearing whatever HP gear you have. Mana is not such a big deal as it's you mana regen that holds you back in Neriak and not you mana pool asa whole.<br>
<br>
Seriously consider taking a couple months to get your epic (of course depending on your guild and friends and all). The epic pet literally TEARS through this place. With KEI I could pretty much keep all the guards and the wizzies and necro and the two strong SK guards in the front by the cleric guild ALL dead. That's 10-11 spawns or so. Just balance out your healing and always keep mana reserved for healing the epic. So you could easily ding all the way to 55/56 in a few days/a week or so, with clearing the entire city with the epic pet.<br>
<br>
Do the Red Wine quest! I can't stress how convienent this is. No sneaking, not worrying about invis dropping. AND you have a good place to sell. All I would do was kill till OOM, then go sell to vendors and fill a bage or two with red wine. Then sit next to quest guy and med while stuffing red wine down his throat. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Even now after all that killing, I can walk freely through most of Neriak!<br>
<br>
edit:I added some details I thought about afterwards.<br>
<br>
Good luck,<br>
